76561198057176782,Not Recommended,224740,31730404,Posted: 13 May,all,Elsabob,"A bit of a mixed review from me, and a hope that the series will return with Clockwork Empires 2.0?  Please?  With levels and a better interface?Good PointsI love the atmosphere and flavour of this game so much. I have ever got such a sense of forboding from a game (apart from Bioshock), or been yelling at my workers berating them for their cultish tendancies.  There is a real feeling that without you managing them pretty intensively, these people would go mad and start eating each other within a week.Each of your people has personality traits, strengths and a history which you can go in and read, which can be hilarious or warn you about events that are about to happen (feeling the beckoning of the waves anyone?)  I also love that it's quite challenging - it definitely throws a lot of bandits/aliens/enemies at you and you won't be able to get through without some of your villagers dying.  Some tips:- Build a pub as soon as possible, because alchohol will keep your people sane until you can build a church- Bury your dead! (your people WILL get upset if you leave them around)- Don't eat the long pork unless you are prepared for consequences- Keep an eye out for villiagers in robes heading for the forest, because they will be summoning something and it won't be good.  Remove their candles as soon as you can!- Depressed overseers (or ones involved in a cult) won't do any work.  Don't leave them with something critical (e.g. Kitchen), take them off it until they've returned to normal- Make multiple barracks and do keep them manned.- Telling the fishpeople to go away, but not eating their caviar is the best way to protect your town - you'll get some attacks but they won't be too bad once you have a barracksBad PointsThe user interface is very detailed but not really explained nor intuative, so it can be hard to work out how to do things, and when you do it can take a long time to do them.  It's also difficult to get an overview of what all your people are doing and i imagine it would get fairly impossible once you get to a certain number.The speed is infuriatingly slow once you've got the hang of the game.Once you've got the hang of surviving there isn't really much else to achieve that really gets you anywhere - no levels and the achievements aren't really enough motivation to keep getting better. You unlock other terrains but playing on them doesn't feel like a different enough challenge - it's just the same game again.  It would be great to be able to expand your empire after a certain point and build on it??The game seems to corrupt sometimes and just won't go past a particular event - everytime you reload and try again it crashes again. You have to go back to serveral loads earlier and try and avoid the event to get past it.  This seems to be happening more now than when I bought the game. For this reason alone I can't really recommend it, which is sad because I do feel like I got my money's worth - I've played it for 38 hours.The random events that happen give you choices, but they are too repetative, so you learn the best options very quickly and then they don't really do anything.ConclusionLots of awesome ideas and atmosphere but needs better user interface and rewards. If it wasn't for the crashing I would still be recommending it because it's brilliantly creepy and intense when it's working (Leave strange objects ALONE people, do NOT touch them)."
