,Not Recommended,224740,11784895,"Posted: 19 August, 2014",all,Lowkey,"Not recommending until: Save Features, fixing common crashes, and smarter workers. Remember this is Early Access though.PROS: Great and open developer who is constantly updating both the game and development blog(http://clockworkempires.com/development.html). Playable up to 2 hours before crash. Witty and fun gameplay with indepth economy/crafting system. Game's price will not decrease.CONS: It took me about 9 hours to exhaust the fun of this game. It probably would be a lot less if it didn't crash constantly and had a save feature. The game is a mix between Banished and Sims if you've played those. Combat AI is pretty good but workers fail to properly prioritize and pick up tasks (I.E. letting crops fail, not helping other work crews, etc.). Buildings are easy to place but hard to edit during placement (sometimes crashes on renovation too). Population and supplies mostly come in the form of ""Immigration"" and ""Colonial Ministry"" events that are somewhat random and frustratingly slow at times. Once jobs or objects are ordered, there is no way to edit them. The price won't increase upon release so no harm in waiting until it's better."
