,Recommended,224740,15109537,"Posted: 29 March, 2015",all,DolgVlaPet,"Didn't played it for long time yet, but as for now I could say that this game future is looking really promising. It reminds me slightly of ""Dwarf Fortress"", only with less features (For now, at least) and graphic interface. Worth every penny and I do not regret purchasing it.Edit (04.05.2016): Some time has passed, couple of patches been released and I've decided to give it another try. Aaand, on the bright side: I loved the individuality in your citizens. Everyone has it's own traits, habits, manias, goals, fears, etc. They could get scared, angry, crazy, depressed, etc. They could have suicidal tendencies, communist thoughts, planning a revolt or a riot against you, join a cult and praise some ancient evil or rob your storages and run into the wilds to form a gang, so you never know what to expect from your citizens and you should keep an eye on troublesome ones... They can make friends and enemies among other settlers and that is a pretty big and not that common feature in games.What I did not like is, there is no subterranian layer and you can only build on the surface and also, there isn't much space for your creativity, as all the buildings are square-shaped and pretty much looks the same. The difference is the utility and decorations, but that's about all... And this is a buzzkill after you got a while playing the game, everything starts to feel the same.Also, the updates are reeeaaally slow. It takes about 2-3 monts for a new update, so maybe I'll check on this game later. But for now, there isn't anything else to report. I loved the personality of your settlement, but the planning/building part is a meh'."
