,Not Recommended,224740,19147128,"Posted: 18 November, 2015",all,The Asparagus Kid,"-----------UpdateStill recommending you hold off on buying.I have figured out a big part of the problem.  The dev team needs to fix the pacing and needs management.You need too many facilities on day 1 and your settlers work much too slowly.  Keep in mind that you start with around 9 people and they all work SLOWLY.* You need a lower class house for everyone to sleep in.  Building it will take about 3 days.* You'll need a carpenter, which gets built relatively quickly but still a little too long. - And assign an overseer to it.* The lower class house will also need beds, so you'll need cloth, which means you also have to build a textile workshop (this is where it starts adding up) and assign an overseer to it.* In order to get the flax you need for cloth, you'll have to make a farm for it and assign an overseer wtih a team team to it.* Keep in mind, these buildings take stone and wood so you'll need to have overseers wtih teams gathering those as well.* You need to feed everyone so you have to build a kitchen and assign an overseer to it, preferrably with a team.* The kitchen needs food to cook so you'll need to make another farm and assign an overseer with a team to it.* There are going to be bandits and fish people attacking soon (even if you decide to avoid conflict, your people will seek it out) so you need to build a barracks and assign an overseer with a team to it.* The CONSTANT fighting is going to require the services of a Barber (doctor) so build that and assign an overseer to it.* Within a few days, people will be complaining that they're sleeping below their station and they want a church.  To build either of these, you'll need a ceramics workshop so build it and assign an overseer to it.* You can forgo the church but it just adds more fighting because of cultists.* Settlers DO NOT DEFEND THEMSELVES - EVEN WHEN ARMED.  This is insane.  Once your guards have been whittled away, a single enemy will slowly destroy your entire settlement.  And even if they are eventually stopped, they kill valuable overseers making it impossible to keep up with the overwhelming basic needs of the settlement.End of update-----------------------------------------------------------Have ""played"" for several hours now.  Moves SO SLOWLY and takes forever to get anything done.  Feels more like a screensaver than a game.I was excited about this game because of all of the hype around the intelligence of the people making it and how intricate behavior would be.  It doesn't feel intelligent AT ALL.  There really isn't any good information presented to the player to help them know what's going on or why.  This game needs a TON of work in making it easier to understand what's happening with the people and the settlement.  Help me out a little.Fishpeople bring me gifts, drop them off, then proceed to attack and kill everyone.  Just keep your damn gifts, fishpeople!  I haven't even done anything to provoke an attack, much less the non-stop fish raids.Settlers with rifles just running around and getting killed by fishpeople instead of defending themselves.Again.... takes forever for colonists to get anything done.  They are demanding buildings that can't be provided because they can't even take care of the basics in a reasonable amount of time.  Waiting literal hours for jobs to get done is insane.As I write this, I'm down to 1 Overseer, fishpeople have been in my town, killing people, non-stop for reasons I don't know, and there is now an army preparing to invade me.  Losing like this would be great if I felt like I had anything to do with it.  Instead, I feel like the devs just have some lazy code in here.FINALFar from intelligent.Far fom done (hopefully).Far from fun."
